1. git init --> To initialize the git
                This command internally creates one folder called .git
                .git is used by git software to identify the folder which should participate in pushing to
                "LOCAL" and "REMOTE" repositories.

2. git status --> This command is used to check the status of the working directory



3. git add    --> From working directory to staging area.


4. git restore <file-name> :--> From modified file to old file in staging area.
                         e.g git restore Demo.java

